Domstein at the Trier Cathedral in Trier, Lautertal]] in the Odenwald. In front of the main entrance to the Cathedral, a 4-metre-long granite pillar, the so-called Domstein. According to a legend, the devil is said to have been prompted with a List to Use in the construction of the Cathedral. As the Dom was ready, he realized that he had been betrayed and flung the stone against the walls. In fact, the old granite columns were damaged during the migration of peoples by fire and had to in the 6. Century will be replaced by limestone pillars. One of the replaced pillars and stopped in front of the southwest portal, and not more was later removed.A copy of the 65-ton columns from the Odenwald Granit is located in the Cathedral adjacent to the Episcopal Cathedral and diocesan Museum.
Bishop chapel between 1245 and 1270, the Gothic cloister, made a connection from the Cathedral to the Church of our lady.The Cathedral of Trier In the West of the cloister the Bishop's chapel (in earlier times, "Paul chapel"), embedded in the floor of a tomb was for the canons of the Cathedral. Today, this place is a stone slab, which is characterized by containing a small peep window, on her OSSUARY MCMXCI.Ossuary under the Bishop's chapel. Since about 1870, the present auxiliary Bishop chapel serves as the burial place of the auxiliary in Trier. The Altar in the Bishop's chapel shows in the Antependium, the "sweat-cloth of Veronica" with the face of Christ.The Altar in the Bishop's chapel. On the Northern outside wall of the chapel is a bell, the gekleppt only to the funerals of canons and weihbisc stations depends will beat (one-sided). The bell belonged to the Domuhr and was used until 1927 to Strike the quarter-hours.The Trier Domgeläute in history and the present.
Church from the music care of the choir music is done by the Director of music, Stephan Rommelspacher, as well as the Cathedral Cantor, Thomas pine. Since 1994, Joseph is Still organist of the High Cathedral of Trier.
Chapter today the Trier domgeist the rule of law from two Dignitären, (Cathedral Provost Werner roessel and Dean of the Cathedral, Franz-Josef't Gebert), eight resident Domkapitularen and four resident Domkapitularen; add to this six Domvikare. All have priestly ordination, and play in the General Vicariate, of the faculty of Theology and Caritas play a significant role. The Trier Cathedral Chapter exists since the middle of the 6. Century, was in the middle ages, a moderately comprehensive, and could prevail with the Bishop to the essential sovereignty rights. Starting in 1289, it consisted only of nobles.In the present Form it was at 25. July, 1884 installed. The Provost is the supervisor of all the Cathedral staff (for example, Director of music, Cathedral organist), and lives in the close to the Cathedral (Domfreihof 4) located Dompropstei. The Dean of the Cathedral for the planning and Celebration of the divine services in the Cathedral jurisdiction.The Trier Cathedral Chapter in the cultural struggle in the 19th century. Century, national socialism and the question of the Saar in the 20th century. Century an important partner role for the Bishop and the diocese leadership played. Its importance also emerged on the occasion of the Holy-Rock-exhibitions, 1810, 1844, 1891, 1933, 1959 and 1996 in a special way. In its meeting of 26. In June 1995, the Cathedral Chapter adopted a number of new statutes, the Bishop of Trier, 29. June 1995 was confirmed.
Regular exhibitions and concerts are held in the Cathedral, such as the International organ days every year in may and June, a point of attraction for many music lovers.
